==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Majestic
<hw>Ma*jes"tic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[From
<er>Majesty</er>.]</ety> <def>Possessing or exhibiting majesty; of
august dignity, stateliness, or imposing grandeur; lofty; noble;
grand.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧The <xex>majestic</xex> world.⟦rdquo⟧ <au>Shak.</au>
⟦ldquo⟧Tethys' grave <xex>majestic</xex> pace.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Milton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The least portions must be of the epic kind; all must be grave,
<qex>majestic</qex>, and sublime.</q> <rj><qau>Dryden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- August; splendid; grand; sublime; magnificent;
imperial; regal; pompous; stately; lofty; dignified; elevated.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 885 --></p>

<p><ent>Majestical</ent>⟦br⟧
